   &UR; PERUVIAN VOTERS DESERVE MORE THAN SHAME AND SHAM &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FUJIMORI'S-FOLLY-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For all the imperfections of Latin American democracy, much
progress has been made in the past two decades in the conduct of
elections. Nowadays, they are normally fraud-free in voting and
voting-counting. Alas, neither of those claims holds true for last
Sunday's presidential election in Peru. In its lack of fairness and
openness, it marked a big step backwards for the region. &QL;
