   &UR; USA &LR;  &QC;  &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHY AREN'T U.S. TAXPAYERS WHINING? IT'S THE ECONOMY, STUPID &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; TAXES-US-SOCIALISM-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It is spring and tax-filing season. This time last year, the
Internal Revenue Service collected $1.7 trillion _ a sum larger
than Britain's entire gross domestic product and enough to ensure
that America had a budget surplus for the third year running. So
why on earth isn't there a clamor in America to cut taxes? The
popular response is: it's the economy, stupid. Americans are doing
so well these days that they don't need a big tax cut. &QL;
</P>
