<P>
   &UR; THE FIRE ANTS ARE COMING, THE FIRE ANTS ARE COMING! &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FIRE-ANTS-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Stanley Schuman was on his knees, gardening, when he
accidentally invaded the space of a fire-ant colony. It was a
serious mistake. Weeks later, his legs still sported blotchy red
stings. The irony is that Dr. Schuman is one of the world's experts
on the ferocious creatures, and of the havoc they wreak. Each
spring some part of America panics about the arrival of fire ants,
and for good reason: they are spreading relentlessly; and they are
very nasty, indeed. &QL;
