</P>
<P>
   &UR; FEMALE-DERVISHES-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   It is another night of devotion at the ancient tekke, as
buildings that house dervish communities are known, in Istanbul's
Uskudar district. There is nothing odd about the scene, repeated
for centuries in tekkes across Turkey. But closer scrutiny reveals
that _ unusually _ these spinning figures include females, banned
from taking part in the rituals since the 17th century. And the
women are not swathed in traditional white but in bright pinks,
oranges and greens. &QL;
