<P>
   RUSSIA-ARMS (Moscow) _ The Russian Duma on Friday approved the
Start II nuclear arms reduction treaty with the United States,
laying the ground for a reduction of several thousand nuclear
missiles on both sides and opening the way to even more dramatic
cuts. By Michael R. Gordon. (With graphic)
</P>
<P>
   (An early version of this story, by Christopher S. Wren and
undatelined, will move by 1 p.m. EST.)
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-POLITICS (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ The opposition was
scheduled to hold its first major anti-Milosevic rally this year on
Friday. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   U.S.-AFRICA-TRADE (Washington) _ A deal struck in the U.S.
Senate paves the way for action on a trade bill that would extend
new trade benefits to African, Central American and Caribbean
nations. (Summary from wires) By Eric Schmitt.
</P>
<P>
   IMF-PROTEST (Washington) _ An examination of just who will be
among the protesters at the International Monetary Fund and World
Bank meetings in Washington this weekend. By Joseph Kahn.
</P>
<P>
   (This article is tentative and may be eliminated later.)
