   RUSSIA-TREATY _ MOSCOW _ The path was cleared Friday for further
arms reductions when Russian lawmakers approved the long-delayed
START II treaty that mandates destroying thousands of U.S. and
Russian nuclear warheads. (Coker, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
