<P>
   WASHINGTON-PROTEST (Washington) _ Vowing to avoid the violence
that erupted last year in Seattle, police here are taking control
of the sidewalks and streets to thwart demonstrators' plans to
disrupt joint meetings of the International Monetary Fund and the
World Bank Sunday and Monday. Some 10,000 activists are expected to
protest the lending institutions' policies that critics say harm
poor nations, the environment and workers' rights. By MARK HELM.
