</P>
<P>
   COMPUTER-COLUMN (Undated) _ Speed has always been the driving
trend in the development of the personal computer. From the
beginning, the creators of PCs sought ways to make them much
faster, and users applauded. Now microprocessor capabilities have
reached a new, higher mountain top: 1 gigahertz, which is the
equivalent of 1,000 megahertz. It's a goal the processor industry
has been racing toward for some time. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN.
</P>
<P>
