<P>
   PERU-RUNOFF (Lima, Peru) _ A look at Lima's pro-government
newspapers last week offered a glimpse of the bruising free-for-all
that awaits Alejandro Toledo when he tries to unseat President
Alberto Fujimori in a runoff election in a few weeks. One newspaper
ran a cartoon depicting Toledo covered with snakes. Although
opinion polls indicate that Toledo is running neck-and-neck with
Fujimori, analysts say that Toledo must brace himself for a
high-octane, dirty tricks campaign from the man who has built a
political dynasty in Peru. By JOHN OTIS.
</P>
<P>
