r l BC-OSGOOD-BIO16-COX     04-14 0222
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OSGOOD-BIO16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The osgood file
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, April
 &HT;    By Dan Hulbert
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Jobs: Has anchored and edited CBS News' ``Sunday Morning''
</P>
<P>
   (9 a.m. on WGNX) since 1994; writes and delivers ``The Osgood
File'' on CBS radio network (not available in the Atlanta area).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Born: Charles Osgood Wood in New York, 1933.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Early years: Raised in Baltimore, Philadelphia and New Jersey.
Educated in Catholic-affiliated schools, including Fordham
University (a degree in economics).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Job history: With CBS networks since 1967, as a radio and TV
anchor, commentator and ``fastest poet in the Western hemisphere''
(in the words of longtime producer Phil Chin).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Books: Five, including ``The Osgood Files'' (1991) and ``See
You on the Radio'' (1999), both published by G.P. Putnam's Sons.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Honors: Three Emmy Awards, including one for his rare 1997
interview with artist Andrew Wyeth on ``CBS Sunday Morning'';
National Father's Day Committee's Father of the Year, 1985.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Home life: Married to the former Jean Crafton for 25 years.
They have five children and homes in New Jersey and St. Tropez,
France.
</P>
<P>
   _ Dan Hulbert writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
