   STAR TREKKING
</P>
<P>
   INTERGALACTIC-TRAVEL-NEW-SCIENTIST _ Intergalactic space travel
is back on the agenda again. A Russian theorist has found a new
type of wormhole compatible with Einstein's theory of relativity,
that can be large and stable enough to allow voyages across the
Universe. By Robert Matthews. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY FUN
</P>
<P>
   HUMOR-FACTOR-NEW-SCIENTIST _ Your sense of humor has nothing to
do with your genes, and everything to do with the way you were
raised, say biologists in London. By studying pairs of identical
and non-identical twins, the researchers found that it was a shared
environment rather than shared genes that makes brothers and
sisters laugh at the same things. By Hazel Muir. 400 words.
</P>
<P>
   WHY SMOKING AGES SKIN
</P>
<P>
   SMOKING-AGES-NEW-SCIENTIST _ Cigarettes are not only bad for
your health, they also give you wrinkles. Japanese scientists say
that smoking disrupts the body's natural process of breaking down
old skin and also causes a drop in the production of fresh collagen
_ the tissue that makes up new skin. By Ian Sample. 450 words.
</P>
<P>
   REDUCING THE DAMAGE WHEN IMMUNE SYSTEMS TURN NASTY
</P>
<P>
   AUTOIMMUNE-SOLUTION-NEW-SCIENTIST _ A drug designed thirty years
ago to treat multiple sclerosis might suppress a whole range of
autoimmune diseases, say U.S. researchers. By Nell Boyce. 430
words.
</P>
