   RUSSIA-ARMS (Moscow) _ In his first legislative initiative as
elected president, Vladimir Putin on Friday won ratification of the
START-2 treaty, which the parliament had blocked for seven years.
The treaty calls for cutting the American and Russian nuclear
arsenals by half. The passage was seen as a sign that Putin seeks a
constructive relationship with the West, but also that he intends
fight hard to block American efforts to revise or abandon earlier
arms-control treaties. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
