<P>
   STOCK MARKET PLUNGE
</P>
<P>
   DOW _ The stock market selloff continued on Friday as the Nasdaq
composite index dropped below a key support level interpreted as a
sign the hemorrhage on Wall Street has a way to go. The blue chips,
meanwhile, also suffered losses when the government said core
consumer prices posted the biggest increase in March in five years,
adding support to the belief the Federal Reserve will raise
interest rates at its next meeting on May 16 _ maybe by a half
percent rather than a quarter percent as in the past five rate
hikes. (Luke, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   DOW-QANDA _ Not everyone who has money tied to the stock market
is a big-risk-taking day trader or big-bucks institutional
investor. Indeed, many, if the not the majority, of investors are
your every day Joes and Janes just trying to make provisions for
the future. What are they to think, and possibly do, about the
market's freefall? (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOW-AOL _ The implications of the big, big drop in the markets
today for the AOL/Time Warner merger. Will this put pressure on the
dealmakers to call off the megamerger? (Kempner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVING LATE.
</P>
<P>
   DOW-HEALTH _ After making 80 deals during the past 18 months,
will Healtheon/MD's pending mergers be affected by the point loss?
(Clothier, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOW-OLD-NEW _ Pursuing comparison between a young investor and
an older one. (McNaughton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DOW-WEALTH _Do purveyors of luxury goods, including homes, fear
a shy away from buyers as the stock market tank erodes some of
their net worth? What do local economists say about consumer buying
habits in light of market volatility? Checking to find out if
anyone's gone bust yet with Consumer Credit Counseling Service.
(Staff, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COKE-FRANCE _ The mayor of the southwestern French village of
Sainte-Marie has set a 300 percent tax on Coca-Cola sales on the
grounds that the drink - the root of a Europe-wide health scare
last year - lacks ``traceability,'' which means the ingredients of
the manufacturer's secret formula are not listed on the container.
(DeGross, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   MP3-COX _ MP3.com, Inc. (Nasdaq: MPPP) an online music source,
today announced that it is acquiring the majority position in
mp3radio.com from its joint venture partner, Cox Interactive Media.
(Clothier, Atlanta Journa-Constitution). 10.
</P>
