<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Page 1, Saturday, April 15. The N.Y. Times News Service Night
Supervisor is Pat Ryan; phone: 888-346-9867 or 212-556-1927;
e-mail: patryan(at)nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead stories:
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Stocks went into free fall as investors had
to digest surprisingly bad news on inflation, the fear of higher
interest rates and the fallout from a a week-long retreat from once
popular technology stocks. The beleaguered Nasdaq index plunged
more than 9 percent and finished the worst week in its history down
25.3 percent. The Dow Jones industrial average fell more than five
percent, closing out its eighth worst week since World War II. Few
companies survived unscathed. By Jonathan Fuerbringer and Alex
Berenson. (We plan to move the story by 8:45 p.m. ET in ``f'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   With graphics and photo, NYT19.
</P>
<P>
