<SLUG> BC-FIEDLITY-LITVACK-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FIDELITY REHIRES LITVACK 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVEN SYRE  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Fidelity Investments has rehired veteran mutual fund
executive Neal Litvack to a position as its top marketing
executive, the company confirmed Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Litvack, 44, will fill the managment void since Stephen Cone
quit as Fidelity's head of retail marketing in January.
</P>
<P>
   Litvack, currently executive vice president of marketing at
Nvest LP of Boston, will become president of retail marketing
services at Fidelity.
</P>
<P>
   He will have responsibility for all marketing in Fidelity's
personal investments group. He will lead the product development
and management of Fidelity's entire mutual fund line, marketing
information services, marketing communications, corporate brand
marketing, and the Fidelity in-house advertising agency.
</P>
<P>
   Litvack is scheduled to rejoin the company April 24. He was
unavailable for comment Friday.
</P>
<P>
   This will be Litvack's second management stint at the Boston
mutual fund giant. He worked at Fidelity for a decade until 1996,
when he exited as executive vice president of retail marketing.
Litvack later took a similar role at NVest, a Boston firm whose
affiliated investment firms manage $133 billion.
</P>
<P>
   Litvack's appointment extends a period of executive change at
Fidelity that began in January.
</P>
<P>
   Both Cone and J. Gary Burkhead left the company early in the
year. Burkhead, a longtime senior Fidelity manager, retired, and
Cone took a position at Citicorp's Salomon Smith Barney.
</P>
<P>
   Gail J. McGovern was named to succeed Burkhead at that time, and
Litvack will now report to her.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-14-00 1958EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT20000414.0361 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 19:58 </DATE_TIME>
