<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-14 21:30 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7458 &Cx1f; tad-z
u r BC-CAR-NASCAR-POLE15-COX     04-14 0408
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CAR-NASCAR-POLE15-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on Mayfield, Elliott after delayed Talladega
qualifying
 &HT;    By Michael Carvell
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   TALLADEGA, Ala. _ It was not planned, but the Winston Cup Series
had its first night event at Talladega Superspeedway on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Due to rainy weather conditions, the circuit's first round of
qualifying was pushed back two hours. It was nearly 8 p.m. as the
final driver, Jeff Burton, finished the time trails under the dark
Alabama skies.
</P>
<P>
   Jeremy Mayfield ended up being the pole winner with a speed of
186.969 mph. He'll be joined on the front row by Bill Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   Qualifying was difficult. The track has lights, but not for
full-fledged racing. The stands and straightaways were
well-lighted, but the four corners were filled with darkness.
</P>
<P>
   At 7:30, fans were driving around the infield with their car
lights on and photographers had to use flashes _ but NASCAR
continued to allow race cars to circle the circuit's most dangerous
track at speeds in excess of 180 mph.
</P>
<P>
   After hearing today's forecast, the sport's governing body was
insistent on completing the first round Friday. The Weather Channel
calls for cloudy skies with a 30-percent chance of showers.
</P>
<P>
   If the first round of qualifying had not been finalized Friday
and the remaining part of trials were rained out today, NASCAR
would have had to wipe out all speeds Friday and determine the
order of the field by owner's points, a championship provisional
and six qualifying draws.
</P>
<P>
   ``Man, this is great to (win the pole),'' Mayfield said. ``I
just can't say enough about this race team. Everybody has worked
hard and I am just so pumped up.''
</P>
<P>
   Mayfield was the only driver able to register a faster lap than
Elliott, who will be making his 600th career start in Sunday's
DieHard 500.
</P>
<P>
   ``It has been a pretty rough weekend, but we had a fast car
today,'' Elliott said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've still got a little bit to learn about the new restrictor
plate, along with everybody else. We really didn't have a lot of
time for practice today.''
</P>
<P>
   The Winston Cup drivers got on the track for just over an hour
of practice. Jeff Gordon was the 18th fastest driver in the
practice session, but slid back to 34th in qualifying.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first time in more than two years that Gordon had
failed to qualify in the first round.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-14-00 2130EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
