<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, APRIL 15
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-BENESCH-NYT (moved on Monday, April 3)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Ruth Erica Benesch, sent by the New York Times
News Service on Monday, April 3, misstated her maiden name and the
year of the death of her husband and collaborator, Dr. Reinhold
Benesch. Her maiden name was Leroi, not Baade. Her husband died in
1986, not 1987.
</P>
<P>
   BC-JDN-REALTY-NYT (moved on Wednesday, April 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, April
12, about troubles at JDN Realty misattributed a statement made
during a February conference call held by Elizabeth Nichols, the
company's president, and William J. Kerley, a former executive.
Kerley said that the company's former chairman, J. Donald Nichols,
did not appear to have benefited personally from improper payments
made to other employees. The statement was not made by Nichols, who
is married to Nichols.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SURVIVORS-HAGGADAH-NYT (moved on Wednesday, April 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, April
12, about ``A Survivor's Haggadah,'` a version of the Passover
story and Seder ritual created by and for Jewish displaced persons
in Munich in 1946 and now newly republished, misspelled the surname
of the retired Brandeis University professor who rediscovered it
and traced its history. He is Saul Touster, not Tauster.
</P>
</TEXT>
