   (NYT34) WASHINGTON -- April 14, 2000 -- IMF-PROTEST-2 --
Protesters against world trade policies took part Friday in
workshops at a ``convergence center'' in a former warehouse in
Washington. The question is whether this unlikely coalition of
protesters and interest groups is, like so many grains of sand
blown together, liable to scatter once its members make a
collective point or achieve individual goals. (Stephen Crowley/The
New York Times) LITE
