<P>
   (NYT33) JERUSALEM -- April 14, 2000 -- ISRAEL-HOLOCAUST --
Eleazar Shafrir, a Holocaust survivor, held papers about land
bought by his father, who died in Auschwitz. ``I'm not going to get
rich from this,'' said Shafrir, who has been trying to locate the
plot of land, bought in 1938. ``I just want justice to be done. The
state should give people back what they deserve.'' (Rina
Castelnuovo/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
