BIZ-BRIEFS -- France's two battling billionaires - Bernard Arnault,
the chairman of LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton, and his
archrival, Francois Pinault, who owns the Au Printemps department
stores - are at it again. Last week Arnault announced that he was
paying $3.8 million for the exquisite French art magazine
Connaissance des Arts. The main attraction for Arnault? Maybe that
Pinault also coveted it. (Chester Higgins, Jr./The New York Times)
</P>
