-- Ramon C. Cortines in his Los Angeles office. In just over three
months as interim superintendent of the nation's second largest
public school system, Cortines has shown himself to be quite
comfortable with the exercise of power. He was brought in to shake
up a system in crisis, and he has. ``He's here as a change agent,''
said one board member, Caprice Young. ``That's why we picked him.''
(Monica Almeida/The New York Times)
</P>
