lesson in arithmetic, saying his proposals for education and
promised tax cuts did not add up. ``Arithmetic is a very important
element in politics and public life,'' Clinton said, teasingly, in
a speech promoting his administration's education accomplishments
to a convention of education journalists in Atlanta. (David
Tulis/The Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
